programme.title: SI Films | Oakmont Unlocked: Golf’s Most Historic U.S. Open Venue
programme.desc:
Oakmont isn’t just one of the most historic courses in golf — it’s home to one of the most exclusive clubhouses in American sports.
Ahead of the 125th U.S. Open Championship, we step inside the walls of Oakmont Country Club — a place steeped in U.S. Open history, whispered legends, and decades of golf’s most iconic moments. From the original locker room that held Hogan’s shoes to the trophies that shaped golf’s golden era, this is a rare look at the soul of championship golf.

In this episode, Chef Jay Ducote brings along a very special fishing buddy, his dad, for our first-ever Catch & Cook freshwater adventure! Steeped in Spanish, French, and Native American roots dating back to the Louisiana Purchase, this region serves up culture and flavor as rich as its fishing. We’ll be staying at Wildwood Resort, hitting the water with Captain Matt Loetscher of Living The Dream Guide Service, and capping off the day with spectacular lake views from their breezy lakeside bar. Hook, line, and sinker — you don’t want to miss this one!
Ready to go catchin’ with one of Louisiana’s best captains? Visit www.LouisianaCharterFishing.com to check availability or book your trip today!

programme.title: Operation Shamrock: Carolina Militia
programme.desc: FBI agent John Osa uses his skill as a financial crimes expert to befriend the leader of a Carolina militia. But will Jim be able to keep his clothes on and hide the wire he's wearing, or end up dead by dessert?
